    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Inspection (Cont'd)"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "CYLINDER BLOCK DISTORTION AND WEAR"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "procedure",
      "id": "proc_cylinder_block_distortion",
      "title": "Cylinder Block Distortion and Wear",
      "steps": [
        {
          "step": 1,
          "text": "Clean upper face of cylinder block. Cover the oil hole to cylinder head with a shop towel before removing all traces of cylinder head gasket. This will prevent blockage of the oil hole.",
          "figure_ref": "fig1",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 2,
          "text": "Measure the distortion of the upper face of cylinder block. Limit: 0.10 mm (0.0039 in)",
          "figure_ref": "fig2",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 3,
          "text": "If out of specification, resurface it.",
          "figure_ref": null,
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 4,
          "text": "If necessary, replace cylinder block.",
          "figure_ref": null,
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "block_type": "specs",
      "items": [
        {
          "label": "Cylinder block upper face distortion limit",
          "value": "0.10",
          "unit": "mm (0.0039 in)",
          "condition": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "block_type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "PISTON-TO-BORE CLEARANCE"
    },
    {
      "block_type": "procedure",
      "id": "proc_piston_to_bore",
      "title": "Piston-to-Bore Clearance",
      "steps": [
        {
          "step": 1,
          "text": "Using a bore gauge, measure cylinder bore for wear, out-of-round and taper. Standard inner diameter: 71.0 - 71.03 mm (2.7953 - 2.7965 in). Wear limit: 0.2 mm (0.008 in). Out-of-round (X\u2013Y) limit: 0.015 mm (0.0006 in). Taper (A\u2013B) limit: 0.010 mm (0.0004 in). If it exceeds the limit, rebore all cylinders. Replace cylinder block if necessary.",
          "figure_ref": "fig3",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 2,
          "text": "Check for scratches and seizure. If seizure is found, hone it.",
          "figure_ref": null,
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 3,
          "text": "Measure piston skirt diameter. Piston diameter 'A': 70.980 - 71.010 mm (2.7945 - 2.7957 in). Measuring point 'a' (Distance from the bottom): 9.5 mm (0.374 in)",
          "figure_ref": "fig5",
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        },
        {
          "step": 4,
          "text": "Check that piston-to-bore clearance is within specification. Piston-to-bore clearance 'B': 0.010 - 0.030 mm (0.0004 - 0.0012 in)",
          "figure_ref": null,
          "warnings": [],
          "notes": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "block_type": "prose",
      "text": "If both cylinder block and piston are replaced with new ones, select piston of the same grade number punched on cylinder block lower surface.",
      "style": "important"
    },
    {
